{"TopicId":212863,"ForumId":196,"TopicTitle":"Escape tower bug","CreatedByName":"Niko_Dragovich","CreatedById":226406,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T01:52:45Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Niko_Dragovich","CreatedById":226406,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T01:52:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EKSP Version\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E :\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n0.1.0.0.20892\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EOperating System and version : \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EWindows 10 Pro\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003ECPU and GPU models, any other system\u00A0information which could be relevant\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E : \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EI7 8700K, RTX 3070, 32Go RAM DDR4\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDescription of the bug. \u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nWhen I\u0027m decoupling the escape tower, the rocket doesn\u0027t follow the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E anymore and start to move like she\u0027s dancing.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nDon\u0027t have the problem with my rocket without the escape tower.\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExpected Behavior\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nThe rocket stay stable after decoupling the escape tower.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EObserved Behavior\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nThe rocket become unstable after decoupling the escape tower.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESteps to Replicate\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nUse the escape tower and a decoupler, decoupling the escape tower and the rocket start to be unstable.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFixes / Workarounds (if known..)\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003EDon\u0027t use escape tower.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EA list of ALL mods. \u00A0If the list is long, please consider using a spoiler window.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003ENo mods\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOther Notes / Screenshots / Log Files (if possible..)\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/nANZ5IpBLkE?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022KSP2 Escape Tower bug\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-02-26T21:54:49Z\u0022 title=\u002202/26/2023 09:54  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 26, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Niko_Dragovich\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RabidSmurf","CreatedById":180026,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T03:18:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have reproduced this several times before realizing it was the launch tower causing it.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nNotice the camera is drifting weirdly to. I believe there is actually broken parts or something and the camera is now focused on some invisible broken part flying off.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}